Drove 7 hours to Buffalo to get a passport and had the privilege to eat at Frankies. Let me tell you ! The best customer services, food, experience I ever had. Kelsey is a sweetheart! Came here on a busy Friday night, but the hostess was able to squeeze us in right away at the bar. Carla the bartender took great care of us - she was so attentive, friendly and conversational that we ended up having an incredible time. The food was superb and the service even more so. Would definitely come here again! Great atmosphere, great staff and delicious food. Highly recommend.

The vibe is casual and the prices are very reasonable. The food was excellent you can tell they make their own red sauce, which has a lot of flavor. I had the Arrabiata just the right spice level for me and my fiance got a dish the Pollo de pomodoro dish, that smoked chicken was great. Also it was nice getting Limoncelo to finish off the evening. Saige our waitress was great we will definitely be back.

Frankie's made out door dining work on 12/23! The staff was helpful both on the phone and in person. The food was excellent, gnocchi was awesome and whatever my wife had (white sauce and pork) was excellent. Drink menu was good, the Manhattan was well made, and the desserts were tasty. I will go back.
Tried the outdoor dining for the first time, it was nice being next to the heater and I brought a blanket for good measure. Food and drinks were killer as usual and the service was great 👍

Amazing food! Best in town! We were in Buffalo for 2 weeks for work and I personally ate there 6 times. The food was fresh, authentic, and sooo perfectly prepared. The environment outside and in, quaint. The staff, all knowledgeable about the menu, including ingredients and backstories to many of the dishes. Love 💘 this place!
I’m Not so sure about the service there.... I had to tell my boss who was visibly embarrassed for me.... to Welcome to ‘being’ Black. 😶

Made the reservation the night before, they weren't booked up but it was a Tuesday night. Went for my fiance's birthday dinner, just the two of us. We had a great time. It was romantic and we had a seducluded table in front of the main window. We noticed they are definitely following covid regulations which made us feel good about being there. The service was a 4 out 5. The waitress was nice but she was the only one there waiting tables so she was not checking us frequently enough (just a small thing). For our food, we got the veal meatball as an app, and would 100% recommend. I asked for them to make me a chicken parm and they obliged me. (No problem at all) It came out wonderful and juicy. My man got the calamari fritti and loved it. Great place for date night at a reasonable price. He got an Octoberfest beer that was yummy. I got a white cosmo (speciality drink) so good. Loved the experience. This was our first time. Will be back!

I had lunch on February 29 a table of 16 when I sat down I asked that with the amount of people I’d like separate checks I myself had 5 people that I wanted on one check the service and food and service was awesome as usual. When it came time to pay we were presented with one bill because the server said it makes it easier for them. Easier for the servers but not us. It caused way to much confusion especially for our last guest who barely ate or drank anything. I don’t understand when a party of 16 come into your restaurant to eat and drink and spend the money we paid can’t be given what we asked for SEPARATE CHECKS....especially when I sat down specifically asked for separate checks and the server said yes no problem. Please listen to your customers we’re the ones who keep you guys in business. My family enjoys getting together for lunch and dinner in downtown Buffalo Thank You  I will recommend your restaurant I always do

We were staying nearby and I wanted Italian. The hostess asked if had reservations and even though we didn't she made us feel very welcome. We loved the vibe here and especially the music. Our waitress was Carol and she was very upbeat and made great suggestions. I wasn't planning on drinking but when I saw their cocktail menu a couple of the Martinis caught my eye. We ordered the catamaran cosmo and a dirty martini that featured not only olive juice but cherry pepper juice too. Also gorgonzola stuffed olives. We split the Kale salad with dried currants, parmesan, pine nuts and lemon vinaigrette. Delicious. I should have ordered my own. We split a pizza which was great but it was pretty salty. The bread they brought before dinner was wonderful. Crisp on the outside, soft and warm inside.

A lovely little Italian. Make sure you can up to reserve a table, as this place books up quickly. We didn't know about how popular it is, and they were all out of tables when we arrived. We managed to find 2 spaces at the bar where we could still order food and drinks. We started with the arancini balls, it comes with 3 big balls. We shared between 2. Would also make a lovely main course. I then had a special dish - can't remember the proper name, but it's angel hair pasta, pecan pesto, grilled chicken, mozzarella pearls and tomatoes. Delicious. Big portion, so I took half home with me. Great atmosphere. Plays Italian and jazz music. Buzzy.

Ate here yesterday with a party of four. We did not make reservations and Shea's had a show that night so it was a pretty popular destination and we had to order from the bar. The drinks were good and the bartender was very accommodating. We ordered and received our appetizer and entries in a timely fashion. All the food was very good, I ordered  arrabiata pasta and was very pleased with the flavor. However all 4 entries we ordered, all with different noodle types, were all far from al dente and bordered on over cooked. The most disappointing moment of the night was leaving and still being hungry after 2 drinks, bread an app and a (full) pasta. My fiancee ordered a half portion for here spaghetti and the plate had no more than four fork fulls of food. The only dish with an appropriate amount of food was ordered from the special.
Great food and great staff. A definite must go to spot when in buffalo! I suggest the patio during the summer!

We stopped here for a late lunch. Wow. Fabulous service. It had rained earlier but the sun had just come out. One of the wait staff, Lauren, was super helpful and desoaked the tables so we could sit outside. One of our party had crutches, so it was much bigger table and a couple of extra chairs. Super friendly and super professional. And the food! Wow! Absolutely delicious. We had two appetizers: the spicy sausage with sweet and hot peppers, the artichoke dish, a Panini, and one of the pasta dishes. Delicious beer and cocktails! Everything was absolutely done to perfection. The only picture that we could get was of the desert as it just came, because everything else was eaten so quickly since it was so fabulous. Lauren also accommodated us as the rain started pouring down and we moved under the outdoor bar/patio roof. This place is seriously a must-see and experience.

As you may be able to sort out by my reviews, it takes a lot to earn less than 5 stars from me. Frankie Primo's is lacking in the area of service. Ordered a pepperoni pizza to go. I ordered the pizza from the bar, which is typical in most restaurants. The next part is amusing at best: When the pizza was ready, it was brought out to the bartenders, which was sat on their counter. There were two bartenders and a student who was learning. The bar was not busy. The pizza sat on the counter for so long that the student was using the pizza box as an rest for his left hand while the right hand was cutting cucumbers, lemons and limes. Needless to say, the pizza was cold when the bartender finally served the pizza. The pizza was burnt on the edges. I do not recommend this establishment.

We were in town from PA for my daughters graduation from Buffalo State (9/8/16).  I had made reservations for 6 people plus a 2 month baby (my mom is 85).  We were seated at a hightop table right across from the bar. My mom could hardly get up onto the chair.   And of course not the best place for a newborn baby.   It was a little rainy and dreary outside but that wasn't the issue.   Directly above our table was a large pipe that dripped with condensation onto the backs of my son, my daughter-in-law and my daughter.  Not too often you leave a restaurant soaking wet.  Not a good experience. Also we had to ask for a refill on the $3.00 iced tea and for Parmesan cheese on our meals. The owner and I emailed a few times; I asked for some type of compensation since our bill was  $165.30 but being that we live out of state nothing was ever done.
